            So, about me, I was born in July 1986 in the city of Renton Washington. I've only been playing Dungeons and Dragons 
            (a.k.a D&D) for a few years, but it is by far some of the best entertainment that one could ask for in my opinion. It is 
            a table-top role-playing game that usually involves something to record your character on, a specific set of dice and maybe
            a figurine to represent your character. All that is left is to have fellow adventurers and the Dungeon Master, DM, who 
            narrates the adventure.</br>
            The game is great because you can be anyone you want to be with all sorts of personality quirks and motivations. The game has 
            all sorts of source material from which to conjure your avatar for the campaign. Below are my favorite characters
            and adventures that I have played.
        </p>
